      <div class="msgContentFrame">My idea is an &quot;OMG I need help with my class&quot; section with links to the appropriate forums. Of course in some cases, their question is pretty specific, but at least they'll be pointed in the right direction and will have a place to start searching for info/asking for help. <br /> <br />Even though it's kinda redundant to have links in there that are on the bar to the right, it would still be quite helpful for new people who don't know how to navigate the site very well. <br /> <br /><a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=6" rel="external nofollow" title="wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=6">Druid forums</a> - <a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=6;mid=1142379200225102855;num=35;page=1" rel="external nofollow" title="wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=6;mid=1142379200225102855;num=35;page=1">Druid 101</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=5" rel="external nofollow" title="wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=5">Hunter forums</a> - <a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=5;mid=1121973706920619605;num=207;page=1" rel="external nofollow" title="wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=5;mid=1121973706920619605;num=207;page=1">EVERY QUESTION ANSWERED HERE</a> - <a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=5;mid=114020566342758114;num=102;page=1" rel="external nofollow" title="wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=5;mid=114020566342758114;num=102;page=1">AZ Math</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=7" rel="external nofollow" title="wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=7">Mage forums</a> - <a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=7;mid=1141749819101828;num=92;page=1" rel="external nofollow" title="wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=7;mid=1141749819101828;num=92;page=1">Mage Talent Specs.</a> - <a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/class.html?wclass=7;mid=1156710688194059271